cs.CV, cs.GR, cs.RO, cs.LG, cs.AI. 

The paper proposes a deep-learning based method for dense point cloud reconstruction from multiple views. This involves computer vision (CV) techniques such as stereo matching and image aggregation. Therefore, cs.CV is the most likely sub-category. The paper also deals with 3D reconstruction, which falls under computer graphics (cs.GR) and robotics (cs.RO). The use of self-adaptive view aggregation involves learning from the data, which is a machine learning (cs.LG) technique. Finally, the paper proposes a novel approach for multi-view stereo reconstruction, which can be considered as an application of artificial intelligence (cs.AI).
